Dinner.
Crispy chicken breast.
I'm not much of a fan of the egg, flour, breadcrumbs routine. I flattened the chicken breast. Painted it with smoked garlic mayonnaise then coated it in panko breadcrumbs. Much lighter than the normal panè. It's also good done with dijon instead of the mayo.
Then I pan fried in butter and a little olive oil.
Served with Violet potatoes. These are not just a gimmicky thing. They are really delicious.
Served with a mixture of wonderful spring leaves. Purple kale, green kale, cavalo nero, spring greens, rainbow chard and fine beans. I steamed all the leaves then tossed in smoked garlic butter.
Some fried red peppers added lovely sweetness.
Sprinkled with coriander.
Light, fresh, garlicky and really tasty. 💖 💖 💖 All the wonderful veggies from @tamarfresh.

Roasted chicken thighs in a bed of vegetables with roasted potatoes and tender broccoli!

⁣chicken thighs 
1 leek chopped 
Half courgette sliced
1 carrot slices
1 large onion sliced
Garlic crushed 
White wine
Stock cube
Paprika 
Olive oil
Fresh parsley chopped 

Add all to an ovenproof dish and cook for 20 minutes transfer to oven for further 45 minutes.

For the roasted potatoes I cooked for 10 minutes. Drain and roast with olive oil salt and pepper, you can add some rosemary or thyme.

✨ Ingredients ...
1. 1 piece of chicken.
2. Fish sauce 1 tbsp.
3. Lemon juice 2 tbsp.
4. Sugar 1/2 tsp.
5. A bit of salt.
6. A bit of pepper.
7. Chopped scallions 10 g.
8. Coriander a little.
.
✨ How to grill chicken ...
Chicken sprinkled with salt, pepper, and grilled to until cooked .
✨ How to make sauce ...
Fish sauce, lemon juice, sugar, mix well.
✨ Grilled chicken is cooked .Cut chicken anf put on a plate, topped with prepared spicy sauce, sprinkled with chopped scallions and coriander, eat chicken with chopped scallions and coriander as side dish.
* Add salad vegetables as you like.
✨ Add flavor taste as you like *
.............................................
.
✨ 材料...🇯🇵🇯🇵🇯🇵
1. 鶏肉 1 枚.
2.フィシュソース大さじ 1
3. レモン汁大さじ 2
4. 砂糖小さじ 1/2
5. 塩少し
6. コショウ少し
7. 長ネギ 10 グラム.
8. コリアンダー少し
.
✨ 鶏肉の焼き方...
鶏肉に塩こしょうをふりかけ、火が通るまで焼きます.
✨ ソースの作り方...
フィシュソース、レモン汁、砂糖、よく混ぜます.
✨ 調理したの焼き鳥を切って、皿にのせて、準備したスパイシーソースをかけて、長ネギとコリアンダーを振りかけ、長ネギとコリアンダーを添えて鶏肉と食べます.
*お好みでサラダを追加してください.
✨好きなように味をたして下さい *
.............................................
.
✨ ส่วนผสม... 🇹🇭🇹🇭🇹🇭
1. ไก่ 1 ชิ้น
2. น้ำปลา 1 ช.ต.
3. น้ำมะนาว 2 ช.ต.
4. น้ำตาลทราย 1/2 ช.ช.
5. เกลือนิดหน่อย
6. พริกไทยนิดหน่อย
7. ต้นหอมหั่นฝอย 10 กรัม
8. ผัดชีนิดหน่อย 
.
✨ วิธีย่างไก่...
ไก่โรยเกลือ, พริกไทย, ย่างให้สุก.
✨ วิธีทำน้ำซอส...
น้ำปลา , น้ำมะนาว , น้ำตาลทราย , ผสมทุกอย่างให้เข้ากัน.
✨ ไก่ย่างสุกแล้วหั่นใส่จานราดด้วยน้ำจิ้มแจ่วที่เตรียมไว้ , โรยด้วยต้นหอมผักชี , ทานไก่กับต้นหอมผักชีเป็นเครื่องเขียง.

Chicken is chicken right? Nope 👎🏼 While there isn’t a huge difference in the calories contained in chicken thigh vs chicken breast, there is a difference in the macronutrient breakdown.
.
Per 100g raw, chicken breast contains 5g more protein and 3.4g less fat. If you’re someone who struggles to get enough protein in your diet without exceeding your calorie budget, making a switch from thigh to breast is an easy way to increase your protein intake! ✅

7 corns dogs vs 3 girls 
LETS GOOOOOO ✌🏻

Finally got the chance to go try out @chungchun.ca for their Korean style corndogs. They were quite good! Definitely gives you the Korean street food vibes 👌🏻

We ordered (in order from pic 3-4) the gamsung (potato), ramen chips, squid ink, chicken, sausage-tteok (rice cake), mozzarella cheese and volcano. 

The staff there helped us dressed the corndog as we weren’t sure what would go well with each. The pairings that she did, complemented each corndog with well and it was so good 😊 

Our favourites of the 7 was the potato and ramen chips. The potato one is like a breakfast on a stick. The ramen chips one was so unique and super crunchy. 

Can’t wait to go back!

Crispy Salt and Pepper Chicken  

 #thefacelesschefuk #facelesschef #chicken #spicy  #peppers #saltandpepper #saltandpepperchicken
 #crispychicken #chinesefood #asiancooking #fakeaway

Recipe

(I chose to brine the chicken first with a mix of salt and cold water) 

Thinly slice 4 boneless chicken thighs
Thoroughly coat in cornflour
Add one whisked egg, and mix until chicken is covered and sticky to touch

In a bowl add approximately 120g cornflour (or potato starch for a better crisp) and 30g Custard powder 

Throw the stick chicken into the bowl, and get messy!
Roll the chicken around until each piece is separate and covered again in the cornflour/custard powder mix

Deep fry the chicken at medium heat for 2 - 3  minutes - as this stage the chicken can be stored for later use
When chicken is needed, refry at high heat for 2- 3 minutes before tossing through “salt and pepper” mixture

In a pan warm 2 tbls salt, 1 teaspoon five spice, 1 tbls Szechuan green peppercorns, before crushing the mixture in a pestle and mortar
Slice and dice one onion, red chilli and redpepper

Fry onion, pepper and chilli, when softened add the refried and crispy chicken, and the spice mixtur, at this stage you may wish to add a dash of soy sauce and 1 tbls sugar for sweetness

It's baby chicken season here!

Chicken and creamy leek risotto 😋⬅️
This was absolutely delicious and throughly enjoyed it, something very comforting about a bowl of risotto.
To make this I sprinkled some @schwartz.uk chicken chargrilled seasoning (1) onto a chicken breast and roast in the oven.
While that was cooking added 65g risotto rice to a pan with a small diced onion and 1 tsp @verylazyfooduk garlic. Make up 400ml stock (I used 1 @knorruk chicken stock pot mixed with boiling water) and add this to the rice a little bit at a time stirring often. After 5 minutes add in some sliced leeks (I used 2 leeks) and stir through. Keep stirring and adding stock until its all gone and absorbed by the rice. Then I stirred through 35g @philadelphia_uki lightest (1.5)  which made it silky smooth and creamy - definitely recommend doing this! Added the risotto to a bowl and sliced the chicken on top, finished with some fresh parsley - 2.5 syns total and a very happy belly, perfect 👌🏻😍👍🏻

McDonald's Three New Crispy Chicken Sandwiches Are Available Now
Following weeks of build-up, McDonald’s has now officially released its highly-anticipated new #chicken sandwiches.
Serving as the fast-food chain’s push for the “Chicken Wars,” the lineup starts with the base Crispy Chicken Sandwich. The new menu option is centered around a crispy, juicy and tender southern-style fried chicken patty topped with crinkle-cut pickles and served on a toasted, buttered potato roll.
Aside from a spicy version drenched with a spicy pepper sauce of the aforementioned sandwich, there is also the Deluxe Crispy Chicken Sandwich. The upgraded option comes complete with shredded lettuce, Roma tomatoes and mayonnaise.
The Crispy Chicken Sandwich, Spicy Crispy Chicken Sandwich and Deluxe Crispy Chicken #Sandwich are available now at McDonald’s locations nationwide.

Crisp🍊 Is a Brand New Pop-up Restaurant inspired by ME, Brandon Donick, located in Hamilton, Ontario on the Mountain. Making friends of so many cultures and backgrounds, trying everything from street food, to the taste of Michelin stars. 

I believe food tells a story, OUR story. It is my pleasure to offer you mouth watering comfort food inspired by all my experience, travels and passion. I will be offering regular features aside from my regular menu and WHO KNOWS maybe those features will become loved and stick around😉👌🏾. 

All food is prepared with the upmost of care and cleanliness, following all Covid-19 guidelines and regulations.

REPOST from @dandyhillfarm:
There seems to be a lot of concerns and questions about chickens during the winter season, so we would like to offer a few tips that we use when the temps drop close to or below zero.

Winter can be tough on chickens, but they’re remarkably adaptable creatures and most standard breeds can naturally acclimate to the cold temps. Though, there are a few breeds that struggle; silkies, frizzles, polish, and other tiny bantams like d’Uccles or seramas. They need a little bit of extra care.

A chicken’s body temperature is around 106 degrees Fahrenheit and a high metabolism that helps them stay warm in the winter. When a chicken starts to get cold, it will eat more, ruffle its feathers to trap warm air, and huddle with others for warmth. Eating more speeds up their metabolism. So it is very important to keep a constant food source available to them during the cold snaps.

Single combs and long wattles, like Eggberts, are susceptible to frost bite and it happens FAST. By applying petroleum jelly or salve, you can help save them from frost bite, plus, they like the little massage too.

Offer nutritious snacks higher in fat and protien. We posted our recipe in our stories. This will provide the extra energy the chicken's body needs to keep warm.

A common mistake when winterizing your coop is that it needs to be sealed up completely. This is actually more detrimental to your birds. They need adequate ventilation in order to release the ammonia fumes created by manure and to keep bedding dry. Vents need to be high and positioned for cross air flow. Ventilation doesn’t need to be complicated. Just seal up anything low, so you can eliminate drafts. A layer of straw up to a foot deep on your coop floor will help keep your chickens warmer. We prefer straw because of its ability to trap warmth in its hollow shafts. The straw will also start to breakdown, which will generate heat. For a heating element, we really like the Producers Pride brooder heat plates. They’re safe, convenient, inexpensive, and multi-use. You can find them at @tractorsupply

Education is the key to understanding. We hope our tips are helpful.

Homemade Tandoori Chicken 🌶️🍗 (Recipe posted 👇)

Indian food is one of the most gluten-free friendly cuisines out there as the spices and sauce are naturally without wheat. Give this famous chicken dish a try, especially if you found the restaurant ones too spicy. Making it at home allows you to adjust the spice level to your preference. 

⏱️Prep time: 10 minutes
⏱️Cook time: 30 minutes 

📄 Ingredients:
🔸4 skinless, bone-in chicken leg quarters 🍗
🔸1/2 tablespoon curry powder
🔸1/2 tablespoon garam masala
🔸1/2 tablespoon paprika
🔸1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper (adjust for your preferred spice level)🌶️
🔸1 tablespoon neutral tasting oil
🔸1 teaspoon salt 
🔸1 tablespoon lemon juice 🍋
🔸1/2 cup plain yogurt
🔸2 gloves garlic, minced 🧄
🔸1/2 teaspoon minced ginger (optional)
🔸1 drop red food coloring ♦️

Instructions:
1️⃣ Cut slits on the chicken leg quarters
2️⃣ In a bowl, mix together all the spices, salt with the oil, lemon juice, garlic, ginger and food coloring into a paste.
3️⃣ Rub the spice paste evenly over the chicken leg quarters.
4️⃣ Brush the plain yogurt over the spice rub on the chicken. Cover and marinate over night. 
5️⃣ Arrange the chicken pieces on a baking tray, discard any extra marinade. 
6️⃣ Preheat oven to 375F, bake until outside browns and inside is cooked through (about 25-30 minutes.
7️⃣ Rest for 5 minutes and serve warm.

Beer can chicken!!!

Not a new recipe but a weekly dinner since Covid!

This recipe comes from the Weber’s Real Grilling, 2005, been making this for a while!!

Never once have we been disappointed with this method of cooking chicken,  you can make it on the bbq (best) or in the oven (still good)

This is the carcass I will use to make chicken stock about a once a month.

If you don’t have beer, any can will do, I’ve used soda water, fake beer, hard lemonade, apple cider, whatever is in the fridge

The rub is also pretty flexible, paprika, cumin, thyme and rosemary are the favorites. 

I use a lasagna pan, 2 birds will fit in this pan.  I do my best to get the bbq between 375 and 400

building your bowl doesn’t have to be hard or complicated! my go-to has been this veggie / chicken / rice combo ⬇️

🍚 CHICKEN THIGHS WITH TURMERIC RICE:
(makes 1-2 servings)

• PROTEIN : 2 @butcher_box chicken thighs (skin on, defrosted) #butcherboxpartner #affiliate

• CARBS : I used ¼ cup brown rice, ¼ cup white rice, & 1 ¼ cup frozen cauliflower rice (my fav combo! cook with ¾ cup water) but you can use potatoes / sweet potatoes / all rice / plantains / cauli rice to keep it low carb

• SPICES : turmeric, cayenne, salt & pepper

• VEGGIES : I used spinach / dino kale but anything works here (shaved Brussels, broccoli, arugula etc)

DIRECTIONS:

1️⃣ rub both sides of chicken with spices, bake at 375f for about 20 min (tbh I didn’t keep track but until it’s cooked thru!)

2️⃣ while chicken is cooking, make your carb of choice! (I’ve been loving making combo turmeric rice OR pouring the leftover chicken fat / juices into the rice 🤤)

3️⃣ prep your veggie! I like mine with some sort of citrus to make it lighter since the chicken & rice are a little heavy.

🇹🇷 Dün yaptiğim Schnitzel tarif çok soran olmuş.  Pratik, lezzetli ve tam çokcuklar göre bir yemek. 
🇨🇦 I hava a lot of request for the Schnitzel recipe. Its quick easy and tasty.  Kid friend food. 
You may need to adjust measurements according to how much chicken you are making. 
✔6 Boneless Chicken Breast pounded and trimmed.
✔2-3 cups Bread Crumbs seasoned with
2 tbsp each  paprika,  cumin, garlic powder, lemon pepper, salt, Italian seasoning, dried parsley,  and graded  Romano cheese. Spread in large pan (or shallow bowl )
✔2-3 cups flour spread in pan ( or shallow bowl)
✔5 eggs whisked in large shallow  bowl
Vegetable Oil for frying
Lemon wedges

Dredge chicken lightly into flour first, then egg, then bread crumbs. Fry until golden brown and place on plate lined with paper towel. Serve warm with lemon wedge.  Enjoy

My newest; a Naked Neck Chicken in High Tops.  This was inspired by a suggestion by Trevor S Robertson. I’m fascinated by rare chicken breeds and this distinctive, quirky and downright bizarre naked neck chicken certainly fits. They do look peculiar, but it’s the way nature made them.  This breed that originated from Transylvania are famous for having featherless necks and preferring pink high tops and bow ties.  I’ll download it on Redbubble at Redbubble.com/people/jimsbirds/shop for prints, t-shirts and stuff. If I’ve learned from 2020 is that having good health means so much more to me now than ever before.  For me that means investing in an alternative to medicine to give me the best chance possible at living a full and healthier lifestyle.  Because I want to be there for every thing that my little boy needs. 

What I’ve learned is that it’s not really that hard to do and I’m not talking about starving myself to lose weight or dieting or cutting out any food groups!  I’ve learned that my body NEEDS food!  I have simply learned how to use it to fuel my body so that it can function better.  I get most of my daily nutrition from a shake that offers over 70 superfoods, antioxidants, proteins amino acids, adaptogens, prebiotics , probiotics, vitamins and minerals and digestive enzymes!  ALL the things YOUR BODY NEEDS  and CRAVES to build a STRONGER and HEALTHIER IMMUNE SYSTEM and  by doing this, I have MORE ENERGY than I’ve ever had in my life! (you can’t put a price tag on your health) I use that energy and follow a 30 minute fitness routine almost every day.  I run an online fit club and pour LOVE and ENCOURAGEMENT into women to become their best self every day.  By doing this I have learned LEADERSHIP SKILLS that I never thought I had! 

I feel like I’ve worked a lot on myself physically.  I’ve been feeling like it’s time to rise up in our mindset and believe we can lose that weight, we can feel better, we can accomplish our goals! 

So In March, our group will be focusing on our mindset and nutrition because this is an important part in being healthy.  I’m inviting you to join me and my group of ladies as we SQUASH those self -limiting beliefs and get ON TRACK with our nutrition. 

If anything you read sparks an interest and you want to know more about nutrition, fitness or mindset, send me a message!

YYC HOT CHOCOLATE FEST

This is the end of my hot chocolate journey, so sad I couldn’t try all of them. I was starting to gain some weight haha! 

Here are my ratings for the ones I have tried:

📍 TEN Degrees Chocolate

CINFUL HOT CHOCOLATE

The cinnamon churro was a nice little touch. I LOVED the cream cheese whipped topping! The hot chocolate itself was okay. Tasted a little watered down (maybe it was just the one I got.) ⭐️ 7/10

📍Hexagon Cafe

TURTLE-RIFFIC HOT CHOCOLATE

This one was super good! Who doesn’t love Turtles chocolate? The hot chocolate had a flavorful, sweet, nutty taste to it, which I loved. And the chocolate and crush pecan rim was such a nice touch! ⭐️ 10/10

📍Higher Ground Cafe 

BLACK FOREST

The drink tasted exactly like a Black Forest cake! ⭐️ 8/10

📍Pixie’s Candy Parlour 

DROP IT LIKE IT’S HOT

The concept was super cute and fun! Although, I couldn’t really taste the caramel and sea salt, tasted much like a regular hot chocolate. BUT if you haven’t already, go check out their store!⭐️ 6/10

📍Monki Bistro

CINNAMON TOAST CRUNCH

Ahh yes. The famous cinnamon bun hot chocolate I’ve been seeing all over Instagram! The star of the show was definitely the cinnamon bun. The Cinnamon Toast Crunch rim was also incredible. The white hot chocolate just tasted like sweet milk to me. ⭐️9/10

📍Yann Haute Patisserie

MADAGASCAR TROPICAL

This one was so different and so.. THICC! My brain couldn’t process all the flavors that was going on, and when you dipped that crunchy palmier and took a bite.. it was like heaven! But, this isn’t everyone’s favorite taste. Too much of it would definitely be overwhelming. ⭐️10/10

📍JusFruit

RED VELVET CUPCAKE & OREO CHEESECAKE

Both were so good! They both had a cheesy foam layer on top that gave it a sweet/salty flavor. ⭐️9/10 for both! 

📍Amato Gelato Cafe

NUTELLA WITH MINI BOMBOLONI

The bomboloni was SO GOOD! And the hot chocolate tasted exactly like Nutella. The whipped cream on top was thick and almost tasted like ice cream! It’s such a generic flavor, but I’m OBSESSED with Nutella.⭐️10/10

And my winner was... TURTLE-RIFFIC by Hexagon Cafe!

This is probably the thing I have made that I am most proud of thus far. These are *plum* brownies - rich and chocolatey, chewy and fudgy, and a sweet, fruity undertone. 

I peeled and seeded three plums (by slitting the skin, blanching, and then putting in ice water, pic 3), mashed them up banana bread style and then added 2 eggs, 1/2 cup oil, 3/4 cup sugar. Then, sifted together and added .7 cup of flour, 1/2 cup of cocoa powder, a pinch salt, and 1/8 tsp baking powder. I made the whole thing in my food processor, baked in an 8x8 greased pan at 350 until my tooth pick came out clean. I really hope you try them at let me know what you think! My guess is this would be easy to do with other fruit chocolate pairings like strawberry, orange, etc. I cant get over that shiny crust. Only 137 calories a square.

📍 Nomad - Surry Hills - Part 2 - Mains

I wouldn’t say all of these are considered mains, but due to the chronological order that they were served, I’ve grouped them all together. Again, every single dish was absolutely stunning and vibrant with flavour!

The ribeye was the most expensive dish on the menu. It was a quality piece of steak cooked medium rare (leaning towards rare). I enjoyed the addition of salsa verde on top which helped cut through the heaviness of the dish; keeping it balanced. The waiter also recommended a side of iceberg lettuce which was actually surprisingly delicious too! It was topped with orange and their housemade shanklish (a type of cheese)!

The date glazed wagyu tongue was also amazing! The sweet glaze on the tongue contrasted well with the Smokey low notes of the tahini! The king prawn dish was great but I wouldn’t say it’s a essential must try by any means.

Besides the proteins we also got the burrata and zucchini flowers! One of the best burrata that I’ve tried; the sweetness of the fennel jam and that robust olive oil really complimented the lightness of the burrata! Zucchini flowers were great too, of course since there was truffle honey and pecorino! 

Part 3: desserts

-
600g grasslands ribeye, vine league salsa verde
Date glazed wagyu tongue, baharat, tahini
Vanella burrata, fennel jam, alto robust VOO
Zucchini flower, truffle honey, pecorino
North QLD king prawns, sugar loaf cabbage, roast prawn butter
For lunch I pan fried some glass noodles with veggies and all the flavorful sauces you could think of. Super easy, super healthy, super delicious!

Indonesian steamed sponge cake 😍

If you have been following, you would notice most of Indonesian traditional goodies use coconut milk. These following cakelettes are also with coconut milk 😊

ingredients

125 ml coconut milk, heat in microwave for 30 seconds

90 g flour

50 g sugar

1/2 tsp each BPowder and BSoda

1/2 tsp Pandan essence (screwpine) and a couple drops of green food coloring - should you be able to find Pandan paste, omit essence and food coloring

a pinch of salt

1 tsp vanilla essence

topping

1/4 c unsweetened desiccated coconut

generous pinches of salt

1 tbsp water

how to

in a bowl, mix coconut, water and salt, heat in microwave 1 minute, at 30 seconds intervals

grease molds with cooking oil, then spoon some coconut into molds

preheat steamer

mix dry ingredients then pour in wet ingredients, stir well

pour batter covering coconut and steam for 20-25 minutes

MUTTON / BEEF SAMBHAR BAZOUN (fried spices) CURRY - Ivan Pereira

INGREDIENTS:
1 kg mutton/beef with bones (cut into medium pieces and washed)
1/2 kg kuvalo (ash gourd)/beans
1 onion (sliced)
1 tsp ghee
salt to taste
vinegar to taste

To grind:

First dry roast: 
3 long byadgi chillies
5 round short chillies (motwi mirsaang)
1 tsp mustard seeds
2 tbsp heaped coriander seeds
1 tbsp heaped jeera
10 pepper corns

Fry in a little oil:
1 onion (sliced)
3-4 cloves garlic

Grind all above with:
6 tbsp fresh grated coconut (can be dry roasted before grinding, if desired)
lime size tamarind or 1 tsp tamarind paste
1 tsp turmeric powder

STEPS:
Boil or pressure cook the mutton with 1 tsp vinegar and salt till it is soft.

In a pan, dry roast the mustard seeds, coriander seeds, jeera, pepper corns, short round chillies, byadgi chillies separately. Keep it aside to cool. 
Heat a few drops of oil. Add the onion and fry till golden. Keep it aside to cool.
Add garlic and lightly saute. Keep it aside to cool. 

Add all the fried/dry roasted ingredients into a mixie jar along with coconut, tamarind, turmeric and a little water. Grind to a fine paste. 
Add the ground masala to the cooked mutton and mix well. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add the kuvalo/beans and bring the curry to a boil. 

Separately, heat ghee in a pan. 
Fry one onion till brown.
Add it to the curry, cover with the lid and switch off the flame. 
ENJOY!

If ur thinking of a Sunday roast - mums gravy chicken is the way to go.

For the marinade of one skin on-chicken you will need: 
1 skin-on chicken 
2 Tbsp of butter, melted
3 Tbsp of Maggi’s Malaysian chilli sauce with garlic 
The juice of one lemon
1 whole bulb of garlic minced

Mix all the marinade ingredients in a bowl and then pour over the chicken. Be sure to put some marinade under the skin for a flavoursome chicken.

Cut a garlic bulb and lemon in half. Stuff the cavity of the chicken with half of the garlic and lemon and place the other halves in the tray to roast. 

Leave in the fridge overnight or a few hours.

Method: 
Place the oven at the highest setting and cook uncovered until the skin is brown and crispy.
Once crispy, Reduce the heat down to 180-200 degrees. 
Cover the chicken in foil and cook for a further 40 mins or until the chicken is cooked through.

Onion Gravy:
You will need to reserve some of the juices from the chicken half way through cooking. At this point also remove the garlic and lemon you roasted with the chicken.

2 Tbsp of gravy granules
3 Tbsp of chicken juices 
1 Tbsp Maggi’s Malaysian chilli sauce with garlic
1 Tbsp ketchup
Water to gain ur desired consistency
And roasted lemon, garlic.

Cook all the above together in a pan until It boils. Sieve and strain into a smooth gravy. Once strained you can also add in some roasted onion slices for extra flavour.

Serve this with your favourite Sunday roast sides and enjoy!

Spice level: 🌶

🫐low-carb blueberry crisp🫐

So BERRY delicious! 

✨ingredients✨

-1 cup fresh blueberries
-1/4 cup pecans
-1/8 cup almond flour
-2 tbsp butter
-2 tbsp keto-friendly sugar (divided)
-1 tbsp flax meal
-1/2 tsp cinnamon
-1/2 tsp vanilla extract
-1/4 tsp salt
-2 tbsp heavy cream
-1 scoop MCT (optional) 

✨instructions✨

1. Pre-heat the oven to 400F

2. In 2, 1 cup ramekins, add 1/2 cup blueberries and 1/2 tbsp swerve sweetener. Mix it up! 

3. In a food processor, add pecans, almond flour, butter, 1 tbsp keto-friendly sugar, flax meal, cinnamon, vanilla, MCT (if using), and salt. Pulse until ingredients are combined.

4.Spread the mixture on top of the blueberries. 

5. Place the ramekins on a baking sheet and bake for 15-20 minutes or until the topping becomes crispy. Serve with heavy cream drizzled over top of each. Enjoy!

✨big thanks to @lowcarbwithjennifer for this amazing recipe✨

Crickey, a year to the day since I ate at @restaurant_geranium. A serious restaurant, one for which foodie trainspotters and bucket-list warriors descent en masse clutching little red books, checking-in on Facebook and populating Instagram with a frenzy of carefully contrived images. Ahem, guilty.

Danish-born @rkgeranium, the acclaimed Nordic chef, explores nature’s perpetual change and beauty. The menu moves and dances with the seasons with local ingredients the backbone to dishes, a study of history, earth, sea and home.

I remember a flurry of appetizers starting with a bowl of crispy leaves and pickled walnut leaves; cucumber water with “ham fat” and snail eggs; and a faux razor clam of which everything is edible, casing and all. There are scallops, oysters and more truffles, an excellent charred potato served with smoked butter, some seeds and seaweed. There are seasonal yellow beets and pickled celeriac, and an entire course during the halfway point dedicated to bread – lots of little breads baked using ancient grains.

Home-cured meats are remarkable too, including the “ham fat” in the appetiser above and a course before dessert which takes the diner through the wine cellar and into an adjoining room where beer from Mad Fritz Brewery in the Napa Valley and thinly sliced duck breast is served.

The food is faultless, and the restaurant a neat and impressive space - lots of natural light, ironed white tablecloths, trendy shell chairs and Danish furniture by Hans J Wegner along with all of Kofoed’s many awards, including his gold, silver and bronze Bocuse d’Or statues.

Read in full at www.civilianglobal.com

📸 Claes Bech-Poulsen
🌎 Copenhagen, Denmark
🗓 December 2019

i went carnivore for this whole month of january, and it was one of the greatest experiences i had. 🥰 i still enjoy this lifestyle, and know how many benefits it gives thousands of people who do it. yet, i did this just for a challenge to see how my body would react - and it did great. i ended up exceeding my “caloric goal”, probably (i didn’t track anything properly, just measured out), but i still felt like nothing was going wrong with my body anyways. 🤪 i was always feeling satiated and full, no hunger feeling (i felt like i should’ve kept to OMAD, ‘cause i was never hungry for dinner after a big lunch) well, i probably used to eat the double than what i do nowadays, which might have been the reason why... if i went back to this diet, i’d perhaps minimize my consume of everything to half, specially my diary intake (i have some subtle reactions to it, mostly allergic). 😕 but i still enjoyed this moment i had, i feel like my body was always fuelled and energised! 😃 yet, after this challenge, i decided to come back to a lower-carb/keto lifestyle, as i think i myself gets more comfortable in it. i’m a big food enthusiast - a ✨foodie✨- and enjoy the most variety of foods, so i’m always trying new recipes and somehow manage to eat something different every single day. but that still doesn’t stop me from being carnivore in some days, right? 😉
-
for this meal i had two roasted chicken legs, scrambled eggs and sautéed chicken innards (liver, hearts and gizzards) it was just so delicious and comforting! 🤩 i specially adore the animals’ organs, and i always try to add them in some of my meals, for both taste and nutritional reasons. 👌

A spectacular 360-degree view of Moscow from the 16th-floor dining room of @whiterabbitmoscow in December last year. @muhinvladimir’s inventive cuisine uses Russian ingredients – think coco lardo with black caviar and black bread, barley porridge with hazel grouse and morels or baked cabbage with caviar. Oh, and swan liver pâté with torched marshmallow (in posting); subtle, seductive, meant only for angels, kings and the grandiose.

The food explores the development of the country’s cuisine (”The Russian Evolution”) with the gastronomic scene flourishing, and the idea of frozen food from the Bloc being shaken away. Many of the staple Russian  ingredients remain - cabbage, crab, bread, root veg - and while the producers and the markets have been in the city for a long time, it’s the application that’s changed - affecting how the culinary world views Russian cuisine.

Chefs now scan the cookbooks of Soviet years with an academic eye, finding lost and forgotten recipes and discovering new influences for their twenty-first-century menus. “Russians suffered 75 years, two-and-a-half generations, during Soviet time, fooled into eating grey, urban grub,” says Mukhin in his episode of Chef’s Table. “I hate that period, it destroyed Russian cuisine. I will do whatever it takes to bring genuine Russian tastes back to the people.”

What you are beginning to see is the clever manipulation of ingredients. Chefs are reinterpreting recipes; scouring markets, forests and oceans in their creation of patriotic plates; harnessing a single component and stretching and manipulating it with wonderful results. Ingredients such as mushrooms, cabbage, berries, honey and so-called peasant foods are being re-examined with menus centred on seasonal or storable produce. Lumb on plenty of caviar with that, and you're winning.

📷 iPhone 7+
🌎 Moscow, Russia
🗓 December 2019

✨Meet Fresh Ontario recently launched their new Peach Oolong Tea series which contain 6 specialty peach tea bags that come in a cute little red can for storage!✨

I’m a huuuge fan of tea and I usually make some for work every morning cause i’m not the biggest fan of water cause it’s too... plain 🤣 This was my first time DIY-ing my own bubble tea since my mom is usually the one who makes it for me 🙈 This peach oolong tea was super refreshing and I love how the peach flavour wasn’t too overpowering; it was nice and subtle which I really enjoyed! I also got to try their mini taro balls and tapioca which were really good 😍 My mom also tried it and said it was really authentic so we’d definitely recommend their tea bags! ☺️

Thank you @meetfreshontario for the letting me try the new peach oolong tea bags and toppings! 💕

I think this might be my favourite cookie recipe to date. If you’re looking for a rich, fudgy, crispy, chocolate overloaded cookie recipe then you have to try this!! 🍪 🍪 🍪 
Double Chocolate (or you can do triple Choc) New York Cookies - Crispy on the outside, soft and fudgy on the inside, packed with chocolate in every bite. Perfect cold or warmed up in the oven for 5 minutes for an even richer melt in the mouth cookie! Did I mention I think I might love these?!? 🤪

Recipe below 👇
230g - Unsalted Butter 
160g - Caster Sugar
160g- Light Brown Sugar
200g - Plain Flour
230g - Self Raising Flour
70g - Cocoa Powder 
3 Medium Eggs 
1 tbsp - Baking Powder
1/4 tsp - Bicarbonate 
1 tsp - Salt
450g - Chocolate chips / chunks 

Method: 
Beat the butter for 1 minute.
Add the sugar and beat for another minute.
Add the chocolate and beat for another minute.
Add the cocoa powder, flours, baking powder, bicarbonate and eggs and beat until it all comes together.
Weigh into approx. 125g balls.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Bake at 180C for 18-20 minutes.
Leave to cook for at least 15 minutes.
Then enjoy!!

This yogurt bowl hit. the. spot. It has alll the goods & is loaded with protein! If you haven’t tried mixing protein powder in your Greek yogurt.. you need to try it asap!!

#dEATS 👇🏻
- @fage plain Greek yogurt
- Chocolate pb protein powder
- Puffed rice 
- @traderjoes pb
- Cocoa powder
- Shredded coconut

Directions:
~Mix protein powder with Greek yogurt
~Place bowl in the freezer while you get the toppings ready (makes the consistency 👌🏻👌🏻)
~Microwave pb at power 5 for 30 seconds to get that perfect drizzle
~Take bowl out of freezer, top with puffed rice (or crumbled rice cake, granola, cereal, really anything your heart desires), drizzle with melted pb, sprinkle cocoa powder & coconut flakes on top & BOOM you’ve got the PERFECT yogurt bowl👏🏻
I’m literally OBSESSED & look forward to this delish bowl everyday 🤤🤩

APPLE CIDER VINEGAR EXPLAINED⠀
So how do they make the nasty tasting vinegar? Apples are crushed and exposed to yeast. By doing this, the natural sugar from the apple is fermented over time and turned into alcohol (like you would do with wine). Sounds like making apple cider, right? Yeah, because the process is similar. The difference is the apple cider vinegar is fermented twice –once to make alcoholic cider and a second time to make it vinegar.⠀

Guys - I think I have found my new obsession...crepe cakes! I’m not a fan of traditional crepes but @crepeetcreme have converted me! First of all, I need to talk about how satisfying these were to photograph - each layer with the cream can be seen so clearly...unbelievably perfect and felt like I bought these from a high end patisserie. Moving on to the flavor, the crepe to cream ratio was perfect for me (even though I ordered extra cream I didn’t end up using). The passion fruit and white chocolate was a firm favorite in my household and had the right balance of tartness from the passion fruit and sweetness from the chocolate. My personal favorite was the tiramisu which a delicious blend of chocolate, coffee and cream -  a bite of heaven! Highly highly recommend you place an order with @crepeetcreme, you won’t be disappointed 😋

.
After planning a roast for today, I got talking to @beckysfood_sw about this dish and ended up scrapping the roast and making it! Plus it suited the sunny springlike weather we’ve had today ☺️
.
So I based this on the @jdseasonings recipe on their website, however I didn’t add the fajita seasoning to yesterday’s order so had to try make my own! (Defo gonna grab a few in the future). 
.
I also switched the bacon for good for you bacon lardons, and didn’t have any penne so used rigatoni. The recipe was enough to feed all 5 of us, plus leftovers (or in our case a second portion for a hungry man 😂)
.
My portion, with the slice of garlic bread was 809 cals, higher than my usual dinner, but pasta always is which is why I limit it to 1-2 times a week. For those following SW - head over to @beckysfood_sw page as she’ll have listed all the healthy extras and syns involved when she made it😘

Spicy chickpea salad. This salad is a winner with the sweetness of the nectarines and spice of the chickpeas. To make the spiced chickpeas I soaked the chickpeas overnight in water, then drained them and set aside.
In a pan, add olive oil and a teaspoon minced garlic. Sauté for few minutes then add 3ml cumin, 2ml cayenne pepper, 1 tsp curry powder, 1/2 teaspoon parsley, Ina paarman seasoned sea salt and let the flavors come out. Add the chickpeas and sauté on medium heat for about 19 mins.
I then added them to my salad of lettuce, cucumber, tomatoes, feta cheese, nectarines.

Strawberry lemon pancakes on the menu this morning 🍓🥞 so light...so fluffy...so delicious!

Ingredients:
3/4c self rising flour
1c fat free plain Greek yogurt
1 egg
1T sugar
2T lemon juice
1/4c water
2 egg whites, beaten
1c strawberries, chopped

Directions:
1. Combine first six ingredients in a medium bowl
2. In a separate bowl beat egg whites until foamy
3. Gently fold the egg whites into the batter
4. Gently fold in the chopped strawberries 
5. Use a 1/4c to measure out batter onto a buttered skillet over medium heat
6. Cook 2-3 minutes per side, makes 9 pancakes

*** Jacket Potato ***
°
°
°
Jacket Potato was actually the first British dish I've tried many years ago and I absolutely love it since then!
It's cheap, easy to make, really tasty and you can fill it with whatever you like! 😋
My favourite filling is mayo tuna/mackerel and egg, but I enjoy baked beans and cheese too.

What's your favourite filling? ❤️

Ingredients:
1 large baking potato
0.5 tsp. of olive oil
Half of tinned fish (tuna or mackerel in brine or in oil) 
1 hard-boiled egg
1 tsp. of mayo 
1 tsp. of Greek yoghurt 
1 tsp. of butter
Salt and pepper
Chopped spring onion to top and salad to serve (I've had Romaine lettuce, tomato, olive oil and spices) 

Method:
1. Preheat the oven to 200°C. 
2. Wash the potato, prick a several times with a fork and place onto the oven dish lined with baking paper. 
3. Rub the olive oil all over the potato and bake for 20 minutes. 
4. Turn down the oven to 180°C and bake for 1 hour, until the inside is soft and skin crisp. 
5. Cook an egg, peel it and chop (or use egg slicer if you have one). 
6. Split the potato in half. 
7. Scoop most of the soft inside into the bowl and add the drained tinned fish, egg, mayo, yoghurt and butter. 
8. Season well and stir until combined. 
9. Spoon the filling back into the potato skins. 
10. Top with spring onion and serve with a salad. 
11. Enjoy! 😉

Mixture for 2 servings: 

-1/2 cup full fat milk 
-1tbsp corn starch 
-1tsp vanilla extract 
-1/2 tsp ground cinnamon 
-pinch of salt 
-pinch of nutmeg 
-sugar (optional)

captions:
Chocolate banana pudding  بودينغ الشوكولا بالموز

Instructions: Pudding:🔸Mix water, milk powder, artificial sweetener, cocoa and flour/corn starch until well combined
🔸Keep stirring at medium heat and before the mixture is boiling add vanilla and mix to be combined
🔸Stir constantly until the mixture is boiling and thickening then remove it from heat
🔸Line a large pan with parachment paper, cut bananas in slices and place them in the bottom of pan
🔸Pour pudding mixture over bananas 
🔸Place 2 biscuits over each other and press biscuits gently over the pudding
🔸Let the pudding cool at room temperature then chill in freezer
🔸Turn over the pudding in a dish and remove the parachment paper 
🔸Roast  and stir 2 Tbsp of shredded coconut in non sticky pan at medium heat until the color changes (optional)
🔸Sprinkle roasted coconut at the edges of pudding
🔸Cut into 8 pieces
طريقة التحضير: البودينغ: 🔸خلط الماء، حليب البودرة، المحلي الصناعي، الكاكاو، و الطحين حتى يمتزجوا سوية
🔸الاستمرار في التحريك على حرارة متوسطة و قبل غليان المزيج اضافة الفانيليا و التحريك حتى يمتزجوا
🔸التحريك المستمر حتى يغلي و يثقل المزيج ثم ازالته عن النار
🔸مد ورق للخبز في صينية كبيرة، تقطيع الموز شرائح و وضعها في أسفل الصينية
🔸سكب مزيج البودينغ فوق الموز 
🔸وضع قطعتين بسكويت فوق بعضهما و ضغط البسكويت على البودينغ بشكل خفيف 
🔸ترك البودينغ يبرد على درجة حرارة الغرفة ثم التبريد في الثلاجة
🔸قلب البودينغ في طبق و ازالة ورق الخبز
🔸تحميص  و تحريك ملعقتين كبيرتين جوز الهند مبروش في مقلاة غير لاصقة على حرارة متوسطة حتى يتغير اللون (اختياري)
🔸رش جوز الهند المحمص على أطراف البودينغ
🔸التقطيع إلى ثماني قطع

Look, we all know how difficult it is to achieve our goals. But nothing in life is ever handed in a silver platter. Behind every achievement is a sacrifice worth giving.🙏⁠

Sometimes all you need is a little push.⁠
⁠
Don’t change the goal. ⁠

Just change your game plan. ⁠
⁠
If you see that one thing isn’t getting you there fast enough... then take a different approach. Look at another angle.⁠
⁠
You'll never know you're likely closer to your goal than you think you are. Usually, we tend to quit when we’re THIS close to the finish line.🙌🔥⁠
⁠
Good things come to those who wait. So, keep going! You got this.💪⁠

MEAL PREPPING & MINDSET

Most of us want to get into better shape, lose weight or improve our health. But let's be honest.......we all  enjoy the exercise part because we get instant gratification. When it comes to food (notice I use the word food and not nutrition to keep it simple) as alot of us already find it challenging to consistently eat healthy and goal oriented. 

The good news is, once you experience the benefits and get into the routine of #mealprepping, you will never want to quit. 

The less good news is, there is no easy way. It requires will power and a strong mindset.

Here are some great benefits of meal prepping: 

- Save time
- Save money
- You will learn portion control
- It will help you lose weight
- Less stress during the week
- No food wasting
- Eliminates temptation to eat unhealthy foods
- You will gain will power to make appropriate food choices. 

Tip: I make sure all my groceries 🥕🥬🥩 arrive on a Sunday mornings, and I use my afternoon between 17:00-18:30 to prepp. Try it, you won't regret!

🍫☀️CHOCOLATE CREME EGG BAKED OATS🍫☀️
.

I keep saying this word at lot recently but I’m not lying when I say this was unreal🤣 I keep seeing chocolate baked oats everywhere and I’ve never made them before so I thought why not give them a go✌🏻
.

👉🏻Mix oats, 1 egg, 1 tablespoon of hot choc powder, a little bit of milk and some vanilla essence in a bowl
👉🏻transfer the mix to an ovenproof dish which has been sprayed with frylight
👉🏻 top with toppings of your choice but I used 1 creme egg 
👉🏻leave in oven for 15-20 mins
.

Delicious and flavourful Indian fish curry with onion-tomato base.
We Indians love to make complicated curries with lots of different spices. But this one is an easy recipe with only a few ingredients.
This is a very versatile 🐟 curry and will work with a variety of fish.

I always use mustard oil in my fish curries as it has a strong flavour profile and works well with fish.
While cooking with mustard oil, the oil is heated to a smoking point and then cooled before adding anything to it.This is done to reduce the pungency of the oil.
All you need is-

1. 1kg Katla/ Rohu or any other 🐟 
2. Finely chopped tomatoes 🍅 -3 
3. Finely chopped onions-3 
4. Cooking oil/ Mustard oil
5. 1tbsp ginger paste
6. 1tbsp garlic paste
7. 1/2 tsp mustard seeds
8. 1/4 tsp turmeric powder
9. Dry red chillies 🌶-2
10. Roasted cumin 
11. 1tsp garam masala powder
12. Finely chopped green coriander( for garnishing). 

🐠 
Marinate fish with ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder and little salt. Keep aside for 30min. Deep fry the fish pieces in mustard oil.

🐠 
On medium flame roast the dry red chillies and cumin and grind to a fine powder.
 
🐠 
Grind the tomatoes, turmeric powder and garam masala to a smooth paste.

🐠 
Heat mustard oil in a non-stick pan. Add the mustard seeds and let them splutter for sometime. To this add finely chopped onions, sauté for sometime till they turn golden brown. Add the tomato and spice paste, let it simmer for a few minutes until the oil starts to separate. Add salt and  water to this and bring the gravy to a boil.

🐠 
Now gently add fish pieces to the gravy and leave it to simmer for 30 min.

🐠 
Garnish with finely chopped green coriander and serve hot with steamed basmati rice🐟 🍚

Pad Thai that would make your enemies cry 

🍜🍜🍜🍜🍜🍜🍜

Actually dead easy this one and only takes 10 mins to cook - couple of rogue ingredients in get sauce but you can just skip them out if they give you the creeps. 

Sauce: fish sauce, tamarind paste, oyster sauce, soy sauce, garlic, lime juice and sweet chilli sauce - if you cba to find all those rogue ones, just use what you’ve got man don’t worry your lil self 

Had to find some rice noodles in the right shape cos that’s what the pad Thai is all about. Soaked the rice noodles in cold or warm water for half an hour and that’s them cooked, just drain and then add to the wok at the end with the sauce.

Method: 
Wok - onions, garlic, chicken, push chicken to one side, add 2 beaten eggs and cook like your making scrambled egg with only half a pan available. Mix, add prawns, add noodles, add sauce 

Serve with beansprouts, crushed peanuts / crispy onions etc 

Mad easy and sure looks the part

@moomoothaimookata Located opposite Paya Lebar Quarter(PLQ MALL), just a few mins walk from Paya Lebar MRT Exit C. They serve authentic 🇹🇭 Thai Mookata at an affordable price. 😊

Choose from 𝐕𝐚𝐥𝐮𝐞 𝐒𝐞𝐭 $19.90 good for 2 Pax, 𝐌𝐨𝐨 𝐌𝐨𝐨 𝐌𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝐇𝐮𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 $38.90 special for meat lover (3 to 5 Pax), and 𝐃𝐞𝐥𝐮𝐱𝐞 𝐒𝐞𝐭 $52.90 to enjoy everything in one go. (3 to 5 Pax). 😄

Must try their unique BBQ dishes from their ala carte menu! 𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐢 𝐑𝐨𝐲𝐚𝐥 𝐏𝐨𝐫𝐤 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐩 in a secret dry rub is very tender and flavourful. And the 𝐏𝐢𝐠 𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬 taste is good that you can't find it from somewhere else.😋

The soup tastes are sweet and flavourful. You also get to enjoy complimentary ice cream at the end of your meal. Truly a great steamboat/BBQ experience.😁

Life-Altering Advice (if you didn’t already know): Bake Your Bacon! 🥓
-
Aside from requiring far less effort (set it and forget it), and producing a far better finished product (evenly cooked), you don’t have to put a shirt on to make it this way. 🤠
-
3 Steps to Success:
1. Line baking sheet with tin foil 
2. Place baking rack on top and lay strips out
3. Set oven to 400F and bake for 20-30min (I usually check in at 20, then keep adding a few minutes for optimal crispness)

KIMCHI STIR FRIED RICE using @jyk_kimchi freshly made kimchi. I wanted a quick meal and decided to have stir fry rice.
Good thing about stir fried rice is you can add whatever you like.
.
I used the following.
Overnight white rice
2 beaten eggs
Diced homemade char sui (bbq pork)
Preserved packet veg
@jyk_kimchi kimchi (chopped) and the sauce
Fish sauce and salt & a it of msg (@mrnigelng )
.
Start frying the (beaten) eggs, then add the rice, stir it so the rice softens, then add the rest of the ingredients and then the seasoning.
Then serve.
.
Are you a stir fried person?
Share if you are a fan of quick meal.
15 mins quick meal
.

captions:
Vegetable Soup with Meatballs, Lentil and Orzo.
Follow➡️ @homerecipes101
Facebook➡️ homerecipes101
-
-
-
-
-
-
INGREDIENTS
1 Lbs ground beef
1/2 Cup olive oil, divided 
1/2 Cup fresh Italian parsley, finely chopped, divided
1 Cup frozen vegetable mix
1/2 Cup onion, chopped
2 Cloves garlic, minced 
1/2 Cup potato, diced
1/3 Cup carrot, diced
1/2 Cup celery, diced
1/3 Cup yellow beans, chopped
1/2 Cup green beans, chopped
1/3 Cup brown lentil, rinsed
1/4 Cup orzo
1/3 Cup broccoli, cut into small florets
1/4 Tsp garlic powder 
1/4 Tsp onion powder 
1/4 Tsp cinnamon powder
5 Cups vegetable stock 
Water
Sea salt and pepper to taste

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. In a medium bowl add ground beef, 1/4 cup parsley, 1/4 cup olive oil, onion powder, garlic powder, cinnamon powder, salt and pepper. Combine well by hand. Form small ball shapes with your palms. Heat 1 Tbsp olive oil in a skillet then add meat balls and cook for 10 to 15 minutes turning them once or twice.
2. Meanwhile in a large pot heat the remaining olive oil and add onions, carrots, green beans, yellow beans and celery. Saute for 5 minutes, then add frozen vegetable mix, potato and garlic and saute for additional 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
3. Add vegetable stock and water. Add enough water to cover the vegetables. Bring to a boil.
4. Add orzo and brown lentils. Reduce heat to medium and simmer for about 25 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
5. Add meat balls, broccoli florets to soup and simmer for additional 10 minutes. Add remaining parsley and turn off heat. Serve hot.

And so the Charleston food tour begins with this pulled pork sandwich topped with the best pimento cheese I’ve ever had!

BEEF PULAO 

#nonveglover #easyrecipes #easycooking #instagram #foodblogger #foodbloggers #keralagram #keralacuisine #beef #beefpulao #nonveg #meat #meatlover #kottayamkari #foodiesofinstagram #foodporn 

Ingredients 

BEEF- 1/2 kg
Salt to taste
Pepper powder- 2 teaspoons
Vinegar - 2 tanlespoons
Ginger paste - 1 tablespoon
Garlic paste - 2 tablespons
Cinnamon- 1 stick
Cardamon - 2 pods
Cloves- 3 pieces 

Put all of this into a pressure cooker for 20 mins or till cooked .

Ingredients for PULAO 

Oil for frying
Onion- 1 thinly sliced
Green chilles - 3 
Tomatoes- 1 roughly chopped 
Basmati Rice - 1 cup
Salt to taste
Juice of 1 lime
Pudina leaves - 1/4 th cup
Corinader leaves - 1/4 th cup
Garam masala - 1 teaspoon 
Water

Method

1. Take a deep kadai and pour some oil . When its hot add the green chilles and fry for a minute. Add in the onions and fry till translucent.

2. Add the cooked beef , washed rice , diced tomatoes and mix well . 

3. Add lime juice and garam masala and add salt if required .

4. Pour in 1.5 cups of hot water. Add the pudina leaves and corinader leaves and cover and cook till rice is done . Add more water if rice isnt cooked , and cook again.

Done .. enjoy !!!

captions:
Open Steak Sandwich with Mushrooms and Peppercorn Sauce.

I love steak, I could easily eat it every day for the rest of my life.
This is my version of an Open Steak Sandwich with mushrooms and pepper sauce.
It’s super easy to make and can be put together in 20 minutes tops.
I start slicing up the mushrooms and shallow fry them in a drizzle of olive oil until they start to soften, I usually add a little bit of garlic, some chopped parsley and a splash of vinegar to add a bit of acidity.
While the mushrooms are cooking we can toast the bread and cook the steaks. For steak sandwiches I like to use Beef Fillet.
I cook it well seasoned with salt and pepper in a screaming hot pan 2 minutes per side, adding a little drizzle of vegetable oil.
Once the steak is ready we can rest it on a chopping board for a few minutes to let the juices redistribute throughout the meat.
At this point I add the peppercorn sauce to the mushrooms with the resting juice of the steak.
When the fillet is well rested we can slice it up, place it on top of the toasted bread and top with the saucy mushrooms.
This is literally all you need to do to get a super easy and tasty midweek dinner.

6 Tips To Make Fat Loss Easier⁣⠀

⁣⁣⁣⠀
1) Chewing gum. A stick of chewing gum contains about 5 calories and it is a nice way to curb your cravings. Sometimes we just want to chew on something, so instead of going to the vending machine for a snack, we can just chew on a 5 calorie stick of gum. Also, minty fresh breath!⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
2) Black Coffee. Black coffee contains caffeine, a natural appetite suppressant. Also, black coffee is great because it only contains 2-3 calories per cup. This number changes if you choose to add sweeteners or cream.⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
3) Strawberries. Strawberries contain about 5 calories per berry and they are high in water. Water helps keep you full and the fiber will also benefit you greatly. Fruits / veggies, in general, are lower in calories and high in fiber.⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
4) Sparkling water. Sparkling water is just water but the bubbly sensation makes us feel more full. An ice cold can of sparkling water is very refreshing and it doesn't contain any calories.⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
5) Eat on smaller plates. This is a neat trick that people find helpful. If you eat food on a smaller plate and fill it up, your brain says "oh, this is a lot of food, it barely fits on the plate" ⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
6) Walk more. Going on walks and getting your steps up is a great way to lose more fat throughout the week. Walking is underrated and it actually burns a decent amount of calories. Going on walks during your work breaks or in the morning/afternoon can really be beneficial to clear your head and burn some more calories.⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
I hope these 6 diet tips helped you out.⁣⁣⁣⠀

According to a study published in the journal Nature Sustainability, the global food system is on its way to drive widespread ecological damage, with almost 90% of land animals likely to lose some of their habitat by 2050, the Guardian reports.🤐😰🤯

Another research by the Chatham house mentions that global meat production could wipe out thousands of species in the next few decades.
Unless the food industry is rapidly transformed, changing what people eat and how it is produced, the world faces widespread biodiversity loss in the coming decades.😲😱😢

Countryvile - a nice walk in the countryside yet again disturbed by the lack of empathy and respect from the supposed guardians of it. A rotting corpse of a beautiful red fox hung in anger after a no doubt unnatural death. The disdain for these creatures so close to a sssi where they are valued is insipid of our farming communities. Overlooking a huge badger sett, one entrance had been half heartedly blocked by wood. The dairy farm adjacent seeped in slurry and the farmer had to get his tractor to scrape a path through it. I really cannot understand people who buy into dairy still. It is beyond the death of the cattle, the spread of btb and environmental disaster. Its given them a licence to wipe our iconic predators out. And their answer? "We feed the nation!" 

And we are extreme? Go Vegan. It takes nothing to be kind to an animal. Even less to choose a different carton of milk in the morning.

🍎🥬🥕 WALDORF SALAD...

Tried & tested by: @sh4k33r4_recipes Mum
📸 Credit: Mum 

INGREDIENTS
6 tablespoon mayonnaise
1 tablespoon lemon juice
½ teaspoon salt
Pinch of freshly ground black pepper
2 sweet apples, cored and chopped
1 cup red seedless grapes, sliced in half or ¼ cup finely sliced red cabbage
1 carrot (julienned)
1 cup chopped or coarsely crushed, slightly toasted walnuts
Mixed Lettuce Bag

***METHOD
1.) In a medium sized bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
2.) Stir in the apple, grapes, cabbage, carrots and walnuts. Serve on a bed of fresh mixed lettuce.

*****INFO & TIPS*****

Some prefer their Waldorf salad made with yogurt, instead of mayo. I usually stay in the mayonnaise camp (which is what we are using in this recipe), but feel free to substitute yogurt for the mayo if you prefer. In which case you may need to add some honey to offset the added tartness of the yogurt.

📝 I adapted the recipe below: https://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/waldorf_salad/ @simplyrecipes

No Bake Key Lime Tart. Thank you everyone for voting in my stories, on what dessert you would like to see today. The banana chocolate chip blondies were ahead up until the last hour.⁠
⁠
This is one of the desserts I lost the footage of that I remade a week ago. I made this dessert with two different crusts to see which one people preferred. Its funny, the crust votes were 50/50. Today I am posting the first way I made it which was with a gluten free graham cracker crust. I will post the cookie crust later on. This dairy free and gluten free dessert takes only 20 minutes to make and is so delicious!⁠
⁠
Ingredients for Crust⁠
1 box of gluten free graham crackers⁠
5 tbsp butter, I used a dairy free⁠
⁠
Add the graham crackers to a food processor and grind until fine. Melt the butter in the microwave, then add the graham crackers to the butter. Press into a tart tin and place in the refrigerator to set up.⁠
⁠
Ingredients for Filling⁠
8oz cream cheese, I used a dairy free⁠
1 tbsp coconut sugar⁠
2 8oz key lime yogurts, I used a coconut dairy free brand⁠
2 limes zested⁠
1 lime juiced⁠
⁠

Everyone has a story…a history…a series of failures and mistakes that have shaped them into the person they are today.  I, for one, believe we shouldn’t be ashamed of our story. Our story is what helped us become the person we are. That story is what taught us great life lessons that we might not have learned otherwise. That story is what will help us make better and wiser decisions in our future. That story is who we are…it is us. 

When I hear others share their life stories, it is those mishaps and failures and even mistakes that end up having the most profound impact on me. Their stories of overcoming hardships, and standing up after falling down…those are what inspire me to want to be better in my own life. Those stories are what speak to our hearts. And how unfortunate would it be if those stories hadn’t been shared by that person….how different would my life have turned out if I hadn’t been inspired by hearing from them?

Never be ashamed of your story and never discount the impact it may have in someone else’s life. Let your mistakes and your failures inspire others to do better in their own life…then feel good about knowing that the things you overcame have helped inspire others for good.

.
Souropod, Staggeringly Good
Imperial Triple Fruited Gose, 7.4%
Confirmed vegan on Staggeringly Good website.

I've been waiting impatiently to try this one after seeing a lot of buzz- the promise of a fruity sour smoothie with a dinosaur on the can got me all excited, and has been sat in my fridge ready for this day.

Souropod TFG pours like juice, becoming smoothie-like by the end, without any head. It looks a bit like a swamp, with small bubbles popping on top as the fizz surfaces. It has a thick mango juice colour in the glass that looks like a, well, smoothie.

The first nose gives a strong sour mango aroma right off the bat. Going back for a second adds in the raspberry fruit and a delicate sea salt.

The first taste is an explosion of mango, tart berries,  citrus and a smattering of salt, all wrapped up with a sharp sourness, with some surprise smooth vanilla to finish it off. As you go your tongue adjusts to the sweetness, allowing the salt-bitter to really sing through before smoothing out.

This basically is a 7.4% sour smoothie, especially in the absence of any hoppiness. This is reinforced by the thick, juicy mouthfeel and persisting stickiness in the afterfeel.

I knew this one would be good, but I wasn't ready for just how good. It is incredibly drinkable - I kept having to remind myself to slow down before I guzzled the lot, especially at 7.4%. It deserved the hype, and now has a place in my beer highlights on VBR. I'll be sure to grab some more of this at some point, I'd encourage you to do the same!

They act as a liver tonic, removing toxins whilst stimulating the kidneys to ensure that toxins are rapidly eliminated. Bile is cleared out, promoting better digestion and discouraging the formation of gallstones. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Dandelions offer a potent gift of vitamin A & K, which are excellent at supporting blood health. Vitamin K ensures effective blood clotting, whilst vitamin A regulates blood cell growth. This wild plant also gives a good dose of Vitamin C and calcium to support good bone health. Eye health also benefits greatly from regular consumption of the plant, due to the nutrients lutein and zeaxanthin.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

•
First attempt at making granola so I found a recipe from @fromscratchfast that used raw millet and buckwheat. The flavors were delicious and neutral and perfect paired with the passionfruit. The recipe includes pumpkin seeds, nut butter (I used cashew butter), and coconut. 
•
I was given passionfruit from a friend’s yard (thanks @holajenylove !) and prior to this meal I had ZERO experience with them in my home kitchen. Before I attempt any real cooking with passionfruit I decided to eat them raw. Wow. Tropical, citrusy, bright, crunchy seeds. Looking forward to learning more about this fruit.

DOUBLE CHOCOLATE CHIP MUFFINS💗
Hi everyone I tried this recipe this afternoon and they came out so well! They’re vegan and can be made using only a blender! 

(Makes 9)
Ingredients:
•1 3/4 cups oats 
•2 tsp baking powder
•1 tsp vanilla extract 
•1/2 cup vegan yogurt (I used coconut yogurt) 
•2 ripe bananas, mushed 
•80 ml almond milk
•1/3 cup maple syrup 
•2 tsp cocoa powder
•a handful of dark chocolate chips 

Method:
1. Preheat oven to 180 degrees. 
2. Place all of the ingredients except the chocolate chips in a blender and blend until smooth.
3. Mix in some of the chocolate chips and leave the rest to sprinkle on the top of the muffins.
4. Bake for 15-30 minutes. 

Recipe inspired by @fitgreenmind 💗I hope you enjoy this recipe everyone! Happy Sunday 💗

PLANT-PROTEIN PROBIOTIC KALE SALAD 🥬🥗💪⁠
⁠
i've been taking antibiotics for acne pretty regularly for about a year now, so getting in those healthy probiotics every day is a really important part of my diet. with the pickled onions, miso, and acv, this is truly loaded with healthy bacteria. plus, since i'm doing more strength training and running, the protein from the lentils and chickpeas means this salad truly hits all my needs! 😤😤 i always feel so alive and ✨rejuvenated✨ after eating big ol' kale salad, and this definitely delivers 
⁠
_________________________⁠
⁠
recipe:⁠
⁠
destem and chop one head of kale (save the kale stocks in your freezer to add to stir frys, smoothies, or more!). add to a large bowl.⁠
⁠
in a smaller bowl, add 2 tsp white miso paste, 1 tbsp of apple cider vinegar, 1 tsp maple syrup, 1 tbsp of olive oil, salt, and pepper. slowly mix in 1 tbsp of boiling water with a fork until the miso has dissolved and the dressing comes together.⁠
⁠
pour the warm dressing over the kale salad, and massage by hand for 2-3 minutes; the warm dressing will help soften the kale too!⁠
⁠
top with pickled onions (i used homemade!!), cooked lentils, chickpeas, and optional raisins for a bite of sweetness. enjoy!

CALLING ALL CHOCOLATE LOVERS. -Our bottled Oat Milk Mocha Bottle is HERE FOR YOU.⁠

As a yoga and meditation teacher, I always felt a little misaligned drinking two lattes a day and trying to get zen. It's like I was personally keeping myself from going deeper into my personal practice and prohibiting myself from coming from a truly centered and grounded place for the CEOs, professional athletes, and other high performers with whom I worked on the mat or meditation cushion. Once I stopped guzzling almond milk lattes and starting sipping mud, I discovered a calm, sustained energy that supported me throughout my day. I delighted in my own practice in a way I hadn't in the nine years prior and I could finally show up for my students feeling awake but not frazzled or wired. If you're a yoga practitioner or committed to your meditation practice, have you thought about setting down the cup of joe?⁠
Blair Atkins, MUD\WTR Community Manager⁠

SUSTAINABILITY⁠
The concept of sustainability consists of three pillars: economics, environment, and society. ⁠
⁠
All three parts are connected by their sub-circles and in the centre of it all is true sustainability. ⁠
⁠
Changing one part of the system has a direct effect on all other parts of the system. The three pillars depend on each other and cannot exist without each other.⁠
⁠
Scenturie is passionate about sustainable living and all our processes from raw ingredient selection to packaging are given much thought to ensure we practice what we preach. 
⁠
To read our recent blog on 'Sustainable Living' click the link in our bio. ⁠

💪High Protein Vegan Meal by @veganfitnesscom⁠
⁠
Looking for a quick & easy vegan meal that you can prep ahead of time? This is perfect and can be done in minutes. ⁠
⁠
Ingredients:⁠
1. 4 oz grilled tempeh⁠
2. 4 oz raw spinach⁠
3. 2 oz edamame⁠
4. 1 tbsp sweet mustard⁠
⁠
Macros:⁠
1. 316 calories⁠
2. 33g protein⁠
3. 27g carbs (10 net)⁠
4. 9g fat⁠
5. 17g fiber⁠
⁠
To cook the tempeh - Preheat the grill to medium. If you've marinated your tempeh, remove it from the liquid and shake off excess. ⁠
⁠
Place the tempeh cuts directly on the grill, and cook them, turning over once, until they are browned but not burned, and caramelized but not crispy; depending on the heat of the grill, this can take about 5 to 10 minutes total.⁠
⁠
This is perfect if you're currently cutting or want a lower carb, higher protein meal!⁠

Just a nice little Sunday morning #veganbreakfast with some yummy veggies tucked inside my @justegg omelette 😍
.
Normally I’d have a huge breakfast and twice the amount of “eggs” and potatoes, but today I planned on throwing back a fresh fruit smoothie afterwards so I’m a little lighter than usual. I assure you, I am NOT light on flavor. 😝 
.
Sautéed fresh asparagus, shallots, baby broccoli, and crushed fennel seeds... then wrapped in a little #vegan egg blanket with some @daiyafoods cheese melted inside. Delicious! 
.
Swipe for the end: I don’t put hot sauce on my eggs... I got a whole jar of @sadiesofnewmexico HOT Green Chile Salsa (this stuff is very hot!) that I love to pour on top at the end. 
You don’t have to travel to New Mexico to get your hands on this stuff- I got mine at @sprouts and I can’t believe it! Get yourself some and thank me later 😘 
.
Happy Sunday!

✨ A year ago ✨ Wanna talk about an inspiring start line - professional runners and the times they accomplish are amazing, something for all of us to look up to for what us humans are capable of, but where the bigger triumph lies for me is the women behind them balancing careers, families (especially moms - wow mad respect), and everything else life throws their way ALL while training and competing at a high level. ✊

This start line of 500 women was without question the smallest marathon start line I’ve ever been a part of, but I could feel women’s distance running and female sport in general being elevated so much in the buildup to and execution of this race. 🙌

When I reflect on my journey to qualify, what I am most fond of is the bonds I formed with other women in pursuit of the same goal. 🏃‍♀️💗 Supporting each other, strategizing together, cheering for each other, and lifting each other up when we fell a little short or completely bombed a race, and ultimately celebrating on February 29th, 2020 YEARS of hard work. 🥳 

And to those who dreamed, committed & pursued this goal and didn’t make it - my heart broke for them - it wasn’t easy and I experienced first hand what it was like to miss by completely blowing up in one race and missing by 13 seconds in another. Qualifying isn’t something I ever took for granted.

While we don’t know what 2024 will look like, what I do know is we are sisters in sport and while we are each other’s competition, we can and should be each other’s biggest fans and supporters. Let’s keep that momentum going! 🤗

Did you know that the labels on our jars are made of vinyl and can be easily removed, normally coming off in 1 piece and leaving very little sticky residue! 💛💛💛

A dunk in some hot soapy water and you'll have a sparkly clean jar ready to be recycled or repurposed in your home and there are so many ways to do it!

We thought we'd list a few to get you started and feel free to send us some pics and we might feature it on our social media pages! 

💛Home made spice mix 

🧡Home made candle 

💛Paint it with glass paints and pop a led tealight into it.... To make dinner nights extra special, hot glue some twine around the top of the jar and hang it from a nearby tree 

🧡Hair elastic and bobby pin storage

💛Screws and nails (you could screw the lid to a wooden beam in the garage to keep them securely out of the way) 

🧡Fill it with compost and seeds and start growing your own herbs that can be neatly kept on your kitchen windowsill 

💛Sterilise them and make single serving desserts, like tiramius or trifle or mini ice cream sundaes 

🧡DIY terrarium, fill with sand and small pebbles and add in some succulents

TODAY IN OUR FIRST DETOX RECIPE: 

FIRE CIDER TONIC 🍹⁣⭐️
Infuse apple cider vinegar with horseradish, garlic, chiles, and ginger to make an immunity-boosting tonic that just happens to be delicious.⁣
⁣
YIELDMakes about 2 cupsACTIVE TIME20 minutesTOTAL TIME20 minutes, plus 1 month.⁣
⁣
INGREDIENTS:⁣
⁣
1 cup coarsely grated peeled horseradish (about 4 ounces)⁣
1 small onion, coarsely chopped ⁣
8 large garlic cloves, smashed ⁣
1/2 cup peeled and coarsely grated or chopped ginger (about 3 ounces) ⁣
1 tablespoon ground turmeric ⁣
1 teaspoon black peppercorns⁣
4 rosemary sprigs⁣
1 whole clove⁣
1–2 dried hot chiles⁣
1 lemon, quartered⁣
2 cups (or more) unfiltered apple cider vinegar⁣
2 tablespoons (or more) honey⁣
⁣
SPECIAL EQUIPMENT⁣
⁣
A (preferably glass) quart container; cheesecloth⁣
⁣
DO AHEAD⁣
Fire cider can be made 3 months ahead; store chilled in a (preferably glass) resealable container.⁣
⁣
PREPARATION⁣
Place horseradish, onion, garlic, ginger, turmeric, peppercorns, rosemary, and clove in quart jar. Crumble chile (use 2 if you like it spicy) into jar. Squeeze in lemon quarters; add rinds. Pour vinegar into jar until solids are fully submerged. Cover tightly, then swirl jar gently to combine. Let stand in a dark spot 1 month.⁣
Strain through a cheesecloth-lined colander or sieve into a large measuring cup; discard solids. Gather up corners of cheesecloth to extract as much liquid as possible (wear gloves if you wish to avoid turmeric stains on your hands). Rinse out jar and pour in liquid. Add 2 Tbsp. honey, then shake covered jar or whisk to combine. Add more honey to taste.⁣
⁣

Here I show you a vegan Jambalaya recipe that is full of flavors.

We prepare this quick one-pot dish with mushrooms, kidney beans, artichokes and use spices that are included in the traditional dish.

FULL RECIPE + TIPS --> https://veeatcookbake.com/best-vegan-jambalaya

Ingredients 
2 pck mushrooms, sliced
4 garlic cloves, minced
1 medium yellow onion, diced
pinch cayenne
1 tsp sweet paprika
pinch clove
pinch allspice
½ tsp dried thyme
¼ tsp powdered mustard
¼ cup (60 ml) beer
1 carrot, chopped
3 celery ribs, chopped
5 cups (1.25 l) veggie broth
1 (14.5 oz or 400g) can diced fire roasted tomatoes
2 tbsp soy sauce, tamari or coconut aminos
1 ½ tsp paprika
1 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp dried thyme
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp onion powder
1 tsp cumin powder
¼ tsp dried dill weed
½ tsp kelp powder
1 tsp dried basil
2 tsp smoky paprika
2 bay leaves
4 juniper berries
1 tbsp Tabasco Sauce adjust to taste
Salt and freshly ground black pepper
1 ½ cups brown rice
2 medium bell peppers, seeded and chopped
2 cans kidney beans, drained
1 ½ cups chopped spinach or kale
1 can artichoke hearts
⅓ cup chopped green onions
¼ cup chopped fresh parsley, plus more for garnish if desired

You already know the negative climate impacts of the meat and dairy industry - but have you heard about #Buttergate yet? News broke this week that cows are being fed supplements derived from #PalmOil as a way to boost the butterfat in milk to meet the rising demand for butter (all that #QuarantineBaking) 🥴🤢

Palm Oil is THE leading driver of tropical #deforestation worldwide - and the impacts are devastating. It is unacceptable for dairy producers to use palm oil to boost the fat in their milk - and their own profits.

Vegan birthday cake for twins. Can't believe they're 3 today

Chocolate cake recipe

🎂150g plant butter 
🎂200g self raising flour 
🎂200g caster sugar
🎂4tbsp cocoa powder 
🎂300ml plant milk
🎂1 tsp bicarb 
🎂1 tsp vanilla essence 
🎂1 tbsp apple cider vinegar

Icing
🎂100g melted chocolate
🎂400g icing sugar
🎂200g plant butter
🎂4 tbsp cocoa powder

I doubled recipe today to make a bigger cake. 

Place milk, vinegar, bicarb and vanilla in jug set aside
Mix rest of cake ingredients and slowly add in milk mix.
Give a good mix to get lots of air in.
Place in cake tins and bake in preheated oven 140oc for about 20mins.
Set aside to cool before adding icing.

This recipe hasn't failed me yet, always light and springy.

Is there a better Sunday treat than fresh, warm, gooey cinnamon rolls? 😍 Maybe this Apple Strudel Cinnamon Roll Cake! Everything you love about cinnamon rolls, but add some delicious apple flavors and more of the best part of every cinnamon roll in every bite...the center! 😋
Check my ‘Classic Cinnamon Roll’ post on how to prepare the dough! Then turn it into this delicious cake!Happy baking and Happy Sunday❤️
_____________________________

1 cinnamon roll dough 

Filling:
2 small tart apples, about 1.5 cups finely diced 
1/2 tbsp lemon juice 
1/4 cup brown sugar 
1/2 tbsp cinnamon 
1/4 tsp ground ginger (optional) 

Plus:
2 tbsp vegan butter, softened 

Optional: Simple icing made with powdered sugar and lemon juice 

Method:
Prepare dough the same way as for the classic cinnamon rolls.
Dice peeled apples very finely, toss them with lemon juice, sugar, cinnamon and ginger. 
Roll dough it into a large rectangle, spread a thin layer of vegan butter on it, followed by the apple mixture. 
Cut dough lengthwise into 3 long strips. Roll the first one up carefully into one large cinnamon roll. Place it on the end of the second strip, then roll it up as well. Repeat this step with the third strip, until you have one giant roll. 
Place that roll (filling side down) into a greased, round baking dish. Push it down gently to flatten it a bit. 
Let it rest and rise for 30 minutes, and preheat oven to 350 F/175 C in the meantime. 
Bake cake for 30 minutes, let it cool down, then drizzle it with icing. 
Cut, and enjoy!

Tepache 🍍

Yep, it’s fermentation again. This is three posts in a row now, but I swear I don’t just sit in a corner eating sauerkraut from a jar. It just seems to be a process I really enjoy and a good lockdown activity. 

Typically made with pineapple skins, this is a Mexican drink. I always feel quite wasteful after prepping a pineapple since I compost all of the skin. However, this drink withdraws all of those otherwise lost flavours and nutrients, potentially (don’t hold me to that).

Think of sweet pineapple, warming cinnamon, cloves and cardamom and spice from ginger. Other recipes I have seen also use chillis, however I gave that a miss this time. 
It’s quite a quick ferment, only a couple of days, so is only lightly carbonated but tastes fruity and spicy which is quite refreshing. It is currently chilling in the fridge because I think it will taste best extra cold. 

This recipe is from @dethample & @rivercottagehq ‘Fermentation’ book.

I’m on Twitter 😂. Follow me over there!! I’ve never been a Twitter user before , so please bare with me as I’m new to this.  But this is going to be fun.  In case you’re wondering how that statement is possible...it’s because the carbs from bread (whether whole wheat or not) are 100% glucose.  Meanwhile what you and I know of as “sugar” is actually what’s called “Sucrose”. Sucrose is 50% glucose, and 50% fructose. Fructose does not go straight into the bloodstream like glucose.  Wondering then why sugar is bad?  I’ve explained in other videos I posted but will make more posts about this topic since I think it’s fascinating.

Today is National Rare Disease day! My name is Victoria and I have a rare disease called Ehlers-Danlos syndrome. Ehlers-Danlos syndrome affects connective tissue, primarily the skin, joints, and blood vessel walls. Symptoms include overly flexible joints that can dislocate, and skin that's soft, translucent, elastic, and bruises easily. In some cases, there may be dilation and even rupture of major blood vessels. There is no cure for EDS but treatment includes medication, physical therapy, and bracing joints. This is why you might see me with all different kinds of braces and mobility aids. It’s very easy for me to dislocate and sprain my joints day to day with simple tasks. I’ve had to relearn how to make my life work best for me and the way my body functions.

Fiber is a complex carbohydrate. It does not break down into glucose thus no calories! Two fiber types: (1) Soluble fiber = soft part of fruits, vegetables & certain grains. It slows digestion. That's good. (2) Insoluble fiber = tough skin of plant foods. Difficult to chew.  Relieves constipation. Most fibrous foods have some of each type of fiber.

Vegetarian brioche Beanburger. 

This week was so relaxing, last weekend as you know I had a huge cooking marathon so we did not think about what to cook one day🤗 which is probably the most exhausting everyday question of the adult life. 🙄 so I had all the time to try something new. A vegetarian brioche burger. 
I used fresh butter of @stamou_milk_products and the brioche was just heaven 😍 
The patty was a black bean patty with mushrooms and BBQ spices from @evripidou.gr. 
And it was heaven😋
Not to mention that bean burgers are a lot more sustainable than meat burgers🤗 plus I was able to produce this almost waste free, as the butter and flour were packaged with paper and all the rest like spices and beans are bought in bulk to reduce overall plastic use (couldn't find it any other way yet). Veggies are of course of the farmers market 😂 (big love story here.).
Please ignore my last blue nail, I am holding on to it like my last will. Nailstudios are closed and no one can fix that, so I want at least my little finger to feel beautiful 😪

IM NOT DRIVING TO LA SCALA RIGHT NOW CHOPPED SALAD

Ingredients:
Romaine lettuce
Iceberg lettuce
Shallots
Persian cucumbers
Garbanzo beans 
Fresh mozzarella or vegan cheese 
Pepperoncini peppers
Kalamata olives 

Chop lettuce finely. Bunch it together in one hand and then chop across. Repeat other direction for shredded lettuce. Chop cucumber, shallot, and pepperoncini into tiny pieces. Cut fresh mozarella into tiny pieces or shred. Rinse and drain garbanzo beans. To assemble salad: layer your lettuce, add the cucumbers, garbanzo beans, mozarella, shallots, pepperoncinis, and the kalamata olives on top. Finish with a light drizzle of the salad dressing below. 

Salad dressing:
1/3 cup olive oil
1/4 cup red wine vinegar
pinch of dried oregano
1 tablespoon dijon mustard
1/2 tsp fresh squeezed lemon juice 
Fresh cracked pepper
Optional: 1/2 tsp maple syrup

Salad dressing note: * adjust volume of each per your taste. Play with it. I hardly ever measure this.

Blended Flavors Chopped Salad 🍓🥒🍅

A Super QUICK - yet, totally unique chopped salad PERFECT for your weekend get-togethers by @cleanfoodcrush 

All the different Blended Flavors happening here in this salad are surprisingly phenomenal together!

If you prefer using different herbs or cheese - ANY type of crumbly cheese or herbs you have on hand will taste great!

Cucumbers are low in calories and contain a good amount of water and soluble fiber, making them very hydrating and great for weight loss and overall health.

Cucumbers are in the top 10 for high pesticides, and are on the Environmental Working Group's "Dirty Dozen" list, designed to help us quickly decide which produce should be purchased USDA organic. 

I recommend that the cucumbers you eat be organic, or local garden grown if possible.

This salad is best enjoyed within a few hours of preparing.

makes about 4 servings

Ingredients:
2 cups strawberries, hulled and halved
1 pint cherry tomatoes, halved
3 garden crisp cucumbers, chopped
1/2 small red onion, thinly sliced
a small handful of fresh mint, leaves picked
a small handful of fresh cilantro, leaves picked

Toppings:
4 Tbsps pine nuts
4 Tbsps crumbled feta cheese

Dressing:
1 Tbsp Dijon mustard
4 Tbsps extra-virgin olive oil
1 Tbsp raw honey
1 fresh garlic clove, minced
1/2 tsp sea salt
1/4 tsp ground pepper

Instructions:

In a small bowl add all dressing ingredients. Whisk really well, until emulsified.

In a medium bowl combine all of your prepped ingredients for the salad.

Drizzle your dressing and gently stir to coat.

Sprinkle with toppings and serve!

Enjoy!
